// AI-UI Component Registry
// Central Map-based registry of all 33 AI-UI React components across 5 categories, with typed lookup, filtering, and validation helpers.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

Module-level: `componentRegistry` is a Map<string, ComponentMetadata> populated at import time
with entries for every component. It is not exported; all access goes through the functions below.

Categories: display (9), layout (6), interactive (6), inputs (11), mermaid (1).

FUNCTION getComponent(name: string) -> React.ComponentType | undefined [2026-03-26]         EXPORT
  Looks up name in componentRegistry and returns the component constructor, or undefined.

---

FUNCTION getComponentMetadata(name: string) -> ComponentMetadata | undefined [2026-03-26]   EXPORT
  Returns full metadata record (name, category, description, component) for a given name.

---

FUNCTION hasComponent(name: string) -> boolean [2026-03-26]                                 EXPORT
  Returns true if the name key exists in the registry.

---

FUNCTION getAllComponentNames() -> string[] [2026-03-26]                                     EXPORT
  Returns Array.from of all registry keys.

---

FUNCTION getAllComponents() -> ComponentMetadata[] [2026-03-26]                              EXPORT
  Returns Array.from of all registry values.

---

FUNCTION getComponentsByCategory(category) -> ComponentMetadata[] [2026-03-26]              EXPORT
  Filters registry values to those matching the given category string.

---

FUNCTION validateComponent(name: string) -> ComponentMetadata [2026-03-26]                  EXPORT
  Throws a descriptive Error listing all available names if name is not found; otherwise
  returns the metadata.

---

FUNCTION getComponentCount() -> number [2026-03-26]                                          EXPORT
  Returns componentRegistry.size.

---

FUNCTION getCategoryStats() -> Record<string, number> [2026-03-26]                          EXPORT
  Iterates all registry values and tallies a count per category, returning an object with
  keys: display, layout, interactive, inputs, mermaid.
